   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <p>FOr the more apt contriuing of this part or branch of the Genealogie, those to whom (from me) the cop<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>pie appertaineth, haue now against this speedy, and second impression of this small Poem diligently perfor<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>med, to which intent I haue set these few lines in the place of the other short Epistle, to cancell the former ex<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>cuse, made for the speedy dooing of the last: whose pro<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>portion beeing (I trust) sufficient, needes no further a<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>lowance then it selfe, in giuing apt bodies to those de<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>scents, in manner as they are truly wouen in the Poem: Farewell.</p>
</div>
